snippet.textDisplay: I got my Chiefs NOW winning 43-27. I had it much closer, chiefs 34-31, but the more I think about it, the 9ers trolls are making my argument for me lol. In fact it doesn’t look like Tevin Coleman will be playing, which to any 9er fan, they’ll think cuz they have 2 other good rbs, that won’t matter and it probably won’t, but not for the reason they think. Idk if any 9ers fan know this about the Chiefs defense, but the first 10 games we played, we were ranked 22nd in defense. The last 6 games we actually went on a record breaking run on the DEFENSIVE side of the ball. We went from 22nd to 7th in scoring defense lol....do you know how hard it is to do that? Imagine the defense played as well as they did the last 6 games, in their first 10! They’d be a top 3 defense without a doubt and Spags told everyone it takes 6-8 games for everyone to get how to do their job....well it may have taken a bit longer? But you better believe Spags has this defense stopping the opposing offense very well.....VERY, WELL. I know 9ers fans wanna backup their team and more power to them. But just do the analytics! This comment may go on for days, but idc. What’s the best thing about the 9ers?...it’s their defensive line. They have 4 very good rushers, that we all know, their DC is a very good one....somehow didn’t get the Browns job, but I digress lol. But if you compare their dline, to my teams dline, I’m not sure I see much of a difference. Chris Jones is the best dlineman in the SB, hate to break it to ya. We also have Frank Clark AKA black Elvis. Those 2 by themselves instill fear in olineman. Now I will say that we prob have the worst line backing core in football and the 9ers are the anti thief that, moving on lol. Y’all Have Sherman, but when I see PFF grading the chiefs CB duo in Ward and Breeland ranked as the #1 duo in football, I’ll take it! Lol then there Honeybadger.....the 1st team All Pro who basically is our leader on defense. He is a SMART, hard hitting, well oiled MACHINE. I will be hocked to see how JIMMY G plays with him eyeing his every move. Now, of course I saved the best for last what you thinkin’ 🤔😎 I’ll say it’ll be fun watching Kelce and Kittle face off as the 1&2 TEs in the game. But after that, who else do the 9ers have received wise, besides Emanuel Sanders....who hardly ever touches the ball lol. He had 2 games as a 9er over 100, in those 10 games.....but the others, he cracked 60 yards once and the rest are in the 20’s and 30’s 😵😳 yikes. I realize the 9ers are a run heavy offense but what if the chiefs do EXACTLY what they did to the Titans, to the 9ers? EVERYONE thought because the chiefs SUPPOSEDLY are terrible at stopping the run, that Henry would get another 180+ yards and 2+ tuddys!....uh uh, only got 69 yards on 19 attempts, lol. That’s 3.6 YPC. Seriously though, I wanna know if there’s any 9ers fan that actually truly believes that Jimmy G., can go toe to toe, with the reigning MVP. Lol and I’ll point out to you an idiot. That said, we don’t like running the ball. It’s not that we can’t, it’s that when you have Mahomes.....why would you ever do that??? Lol but d Williams is no slouch. So that leaves us with, the cheetah, Watkins and Hardman.......I think they call that “an embarrassment of riches?” Lol. I think if anyone read all this, that ya get my point(s) Chiefs got this.

snippet.textDisplay:
GB was lucky this year.

1. Facing KC without Mahomes.

2. Facing Min the second time with no dalvin cook.

3. Both games against Detroit were close to losses and phantom penalties helped them win. Especially that second Det game.

4. Because of that + easy schedule, they slid into the 2 seed. They got to host Seattle on rest, Seattle lives and dies by Wilson so they werent a legit SB contender in anyone's mind. And GB still let them come back and have the ball with a chance to win.

The Packers have talent and they were definitely worthy of being in the playoffs but the reality is that they had a lot of things fall into place for them this year that helped get them to that 13 and 3 record. I feel 9-7 or 10-6 was more what they looked like.
